
1. What is Linear Regression in simple words?

Linear Regression models linear relationships between independent variables (X) and dependent variable (y) using the equation:


y = β₀ + β₁X₁ + β₂X₂ + ... + βₙXₙ + ε

Key Components:

    β₀: Intercept (baseline value when all X=0)

    βᵢ: Coefficients (change in y per unit change in Xᵢ)

    ε: Error term (unmodeled variance)

Optimization: Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) minimizes sum of squared residuals:


min Σ(yᵢ - ŷᵢ)²



2. Why do we use Linear Regression for salary prediction?

Salary exhibits linear relationships with quantifiable factors:

| Feature          | Expected Coefficient | Business Logic           |
| ---------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------ |
| experience_years | +₹2.5L/year          | Domain expertise premium |
| education_level  | +₹3L/degree          | Qualification signaling  |
| department       | +₹1-5L               | Market demand variance   |
| company_tenure   | +₹0.8L/year          | Loyalty/stability bonus  |

